{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox officeholder | name = Charlie Aptroot | image = CAptroot.jpg | imagesize = 200px | office = [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|Member of the House of Representatives]] | term_start = 30 January 2003 | term_end = 19 September 2012 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|09|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[The Hague]], [[Netherlands]] | death_date = | death_place = | birthname = Charles Bernhard Aptroot | nationality = [[Netherlands|Dutch]] | party = [[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]] | spouse = Married | residence = [[Wassenaar]], [[Netherlands]] | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Politician]], [[Civil service|civil servant]], [[businessperson]], [[teacher]] | signature = | website = {{nl}} [http://www.charlieaptroot.nl/ Official site] }}
'''Charles Bernhard "Charlie" Aptroot''' (born 30 September 1950) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] politician of the [[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]] (VVD). He was a [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|Member of the House of Representatives]] from 30 January 2003 to 19 September 2012. He focused on matters of [[traffic]], [[public transport]] and [[Ministry of Internal Affairs|internal affairs]].<ref>{{nl}} [http://www.vvd.nl/mensen/detail/13/charlie-aptroot Charlie Aptroot] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110321110115/http://www.vvd.nl/mensen/detail/13/charlie-aptroot |date=March 21, 2011 }} ''[[People's Party for Freedom and Democracy]]''</ref> Since 1 September 2012 he has been [[burgemeester|mayor]] of [[Zoetermeer]].
Aptroot was elected into the House of Representatives in the [[Dutch general election, 2003|general election of 2003]]. In 2010 he contested in the election for [[Speaker of the House of Representatives (Netherlands)|Speaker of the House of Representatives]], but was defeated by incumbent Speaker [[Gerdi Verbeet]].<ref>{{nl}} [http://nos.nl/artikel/166486-twee-kandidaatvoorzitters-tweede-kamer.html Twee kandidaat-voorzitters Tweede Kamer], [[Netherlands Broadcasting Foundation|NOS]], 22 June 2010</ref>
In the past Aptroot was a member of the [[municipal council]] of [[Wassenaar]] from 1982 to 1998 and an [[alderman]] of the same municipality from 1990 to 1996. He was also a member of the [[States of South Holland]] from 1999 to 2003.
From 1978 to 2001 Aptroot was together with his brother director of the [[Jonco-groep]], a [[wholesale]] in [[mercery]] in [[Rotterdam]].
